f_{X}(x)=\int_0^{1-x}\frac{1}{2}dy=\frac{1-x}{2} \quad \text{for $0<x<1$}
f_{Y}(y)=\int_0^{1-y}\frac{1}{2}dx=\frac{1-y}{2} \quad \text{for $0<y<1$}.
\mathbb{E}(Y|X=x)=\int_0^{1-x}y(1-x)dy=-\frac{1}{2}(x-1)^3 (=\mathbb{E}Y?).
